          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>1 fol.; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: KFQ 39A; Lines per page: 7; Dimensions: 120 x 180 mm; Qurʾānic Text: Q 31:16-20; Script style: kūfī D; Estimated date of production: 800-1000.</p>
              <p>Cf. entry by François Déroche about fragment KFQ 39A (Déroche, <ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/QJQEKNSJ" sameAs="QJQEKNSJ" type="zotero">The Abbasid Tradition, London 1992</ref>, p. 107): "53 / Single folio / 9th or 10th century AD / 12 x 18 cm, with 7 lines to the page / <hi rend="italic">Material</hi> Parchment; the verso is the hair side / <hi rend="italic">Text</hi> <hi rend="italic">area</hi> 6.8 x 13.5cm / <hi rend="italic">Script</hi> A variant of group D / <hi rend="italic">Accession</hi> <hi rend="italic">no</hi>. KFQ 39A / The text – verses 16-20 of <hi rend="italic">Sūrat</hi> <hi rend="italic">Luqmān</hi> (XXXI) – is written in dark brown ink, with diacritical strokes added. Red dots indicate the vocalization. The verses are not punctuated. The upper outer corner has been damaged.”</p>
              <p><ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/1039/page/1r?sura=31&amp;verse=16">KFQ 39A</ref> and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/1040/page/1r?sura=51&amp;verse=7">KFQ 39B</ref> are similar in script style but belong two distinct codices.  </p>
            </summary>
